## 19. API SPECIFICATION

### 19.1 Public API (for external integrations)

```
Authentication: Bearer {apiKey} or ?api_key={apiKey}

GET    /api/v1/pages                    → List pages
GET    /api/v1/pages/:id                → Get page detail
POST   /api/v1/pages                    → Create page
PATCH  /api/v1/pages/:id                → Update page
DELETE /api/v1/pages/:id                → Delete page
POST   /api/v1/pages/:id/publish        → Publish page

GET    /api/v1/contacts                 → List contacts (paginated)
GET    /api/v1/contacts/:id             → Get contact
POST   /api/v1/contacts                 → Create/upsert contact
PATCH  /api/v1/contacts/:id             → Update contact
POST   /api/v1/contacts/:id/tags        → Add tags
DELETE /api/v1/contacts/:id/tags/:tag   → Remove tag

GET    /api/v1/segments                 → List segments
GET    /api/v1/segments/:id/contacts    → Get contacts in segment

GET    /api/v1/experiments              → List experiments
GET    /api/v1/experiments/:id          → Get experiment + results
POST   /api/v1/experiments/:id/start    → Start experiment
POST   /api/v1/experiments/:id/stop     → Stop experiment

GET    /api/v1/analytics/summary        → Summary stats
GET    /api/v1/analytics/pages          → Per-page stats
GET    /api/v1/analytics/sources        → Traffic source breakdown

POST   /api/v1/events                   → Track custom event
POST   /api/v1/submissions              → Submit form data

GET    /api/v1/templates                → List templates
POST   /api/v1/pages/from-template      → Create page from template
```

